# mbuzz

> Multi-touch attribution that shows the model behind every number. Every other attribution tool runs a single hidden model and calls the answer truth. mbuzz runs eight models side-by-side — first-touch, last-touch, linear, time-decay, position-based, Markov, Shapley, data-driven — and lets you write your own in a SQL-like Attribution DSL. Open-source SDKs for Ruby, Node, Python, and PHP. Server-side accurate, developer-owned, honestly priced.

## What mbuzz does

- Captures 30–40% more touchpoints than client-side tools by running entirely server-side (ad-blocker proof, iOS-private proof, cross-domain solid)
- Runs eight attribution models on the same data simultaneously: first-touch, last-touch, linear, time-decay, position-based, Markov chain, Shapley value, data-driven
- Lets technical marketers fork any of the eight built-in models or write their own in the Attribution DSL — a SQL-like language with nested time windows, custom decay curves, and segment-specific logic
- Customers own and can export their data on every plan via CSV, API, and an MCP server for agent-native pulls

## Who it is for

Technical marketers, marketing operations, growth engineers, and data-savvy CMOs at $1M–$100M revenue companies spending $20K–$1M per month on paid media. Too small for Haus / Measured / Mutinex enterprise MMM ($10K–$132K per year). Too sophisticated for GA4 alone.

## Pricing

- Free: $0/month — 30,000 events, all 8 attribution models, 0 custom DSL models, 0 ad platform integrations
- Starter: $29/month — 1,000,000 events, 3 custom DSL models, 2 ad platform integrations, $5 per 250K overage
- Growth: $99/month — 5,000,000 events, 5 custom DSL models, 5 ad platform integrations, $15 per 1M overage
- Pro: $299/month — 25,000,000 events, 10 custom DSL models, unlimited ad platform integrations, $50 per 5M overage

Machine-readable pricing: https://mbuzz.co/pricing.md

